				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^{12}$$\end{document}12 W/cm² to 10\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$^{14}$$\end{document}14 W/cm² corresponding to characteristic time intervals of 10 ps to 30 fs10. Thus, temporal contrast requirements grow with peak intensity. For a 1 PW system focused with short focal length optics, the corresponding intensities approach 10\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
